# Proxy API calls through this same origin (200 status = transparent proxy,
# not a client-side redirect — see https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/#proxying).
#
# Without this, the browser talks to omnomnom-api.wasim-811.workers.dev
# directly, a different registrable domain from omnomnom.pages.dev. That
# makes the refresh-token cookie third-party from the browser's point of
# view, which Safari's Intelligent Tracking Prevention blocks outright
# regardless of SameSite=None — silently breaking persistent login on iOS.
# Proxying makes every request same-origin, so the cookie is first-party.
/api/*  https://omnomnom-api.wasim-811.workers.dev/api/:splat  200
